<constraints>
- Comprehensive but focused. Target 500-1000 lines.
- Reference the existing stack, architecture, and patterns from the brownfield scan.
- API endpoints must specify method, path, request body, and response shape.
- Data model must show entity fields with types and relationships.
- Implementation plan must be phased — each phase must be independently deployable or testable.
- Task list must be a markdown table with numeric IDs, priority (High/Medium/Low), and time estimate.
- Testing strategy must name the test framework detected in the brownfield scan.
- Do not document parts of the system unrelated to the feature being specified.
</constraints>

<output_format>
Generate a Markdown document with YAML frontmatter followed by exactly these sections.
Do NOT wrap in markdown code fences.

