# {{projectName}} — Specification

## Overview
[Project/feature description, goals, and target users — 3-5 sentences.
What problem does this solve? Who benefits? What are the success criteria?]

## Technical Design

### Architecture
[High-level architecture decisions. Reference the detected pattern (monolith/modular/monorepo/etc.)
from the brownfield scan. Describe how this feature fits into the existing structure.
Include a simple ASCII or Mermaid diagram if the flow is non-trivial.]

### API / Endpoints
[List each endpoint with method, path, description, request body, and response shape.
Format as a table or code blocks. If no API is involved, describe the interface contract instead.]

### Data Model
[Schema, entities, and relationships relevant to this feature.
Show field names and types. Reference existing models from the brownfield scan where applicable.]

### Dependencies
[External services, libraries, or internal modules this feature depends on.
Reference versions from the detected package manager manifest where known.]

## Implementation Plan

### Phase 1: [Descriptive Name]
[What gets built in phase 1. Must be independently testable.
List the key files to create or modify.]

### Phase 2: [Descriptive Name]
[What gets built in phase 2. Depends on phase 1 being complete.
List the key files to create or modify.]

[Add Phase 3+ only if genuinely needed for this feature scope]

## Testing Strategy
[Test approach for this feature. Reference the detected test framework.
Specify: unit tests (which modules), integration tests (which flows), E2E tests (which user journeys).
State coverage target as a percentage.]

## Task List
| # | Task | Priority | Estimate |
